<F P=106> [Article signed DT/WI/PI: "Maintenance of Goesgen Nuclear </F>
Plant -- One-Third of Fuel Elements To Be Changed"] 
  [Text] Goesgen, 3 Jun (ATS) -- The maintenance of the 
Goesgen Nuclear Plant will start on Saturday [4 June]. 
One-third of the fuel elements will be changed and many 
fucntions will be performed. The production of electricity will 
resume in July, according to a press release issued by the 
plant's management on Friday. 
  The plant's production reached 98.8 percent of capacity 
during the last 335 days of the cycle, amounting to 7.382 
trillion kWh. This represents 15 percent of Switzerland's 
electricity needs. These "remarkable" figures are due to the 
plant's excellent condition and reliability, according to the 
press release. 

